<br>
Lex observed Chloe as she walked into the Talon and strode up to the counter, where she flashed Lana a bright smile. Clark had told him that Lana was now staying with Chloe and her dad until she finished high school. Lex seemed intrigued at the thought that Chloe could put her feelings for Clark aside and be friends with the girl he had a crush on. It certainly showed a character of spirit that most people didn't possess, himself included. Lex turned to Clark and smirked when he noticed that Clark was stealing a glimpse of Lana without her knowledge.<br>
<br>
&quot;Chloe seems happy,&quot; Lex said in an intentionally emotionless tone. Clark looked over at him and raised his eyebrows.<br>
<br>
&quot;Guess that's what love does to you,&quot; Clark said. Lex couldn't hide the surprise that flickered over his features.<br>
<br>
&quot;So it was Miss Sullivan that you were staring at just now?&quot; He asked. Lex thought Clark was still hung up on Lana. Entertaining the thought of Clark being with Chloe, the girl his own thoughts had been drifting to recently, was truthfully, a little troublesome. Clark blushed and his eyes widened.<br>
<br>
&quot;Uh, no, I,&quot; Clark stammered. Lex smirked again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lana,&quot; Lex answered for him. Clark blushed again and nodded. Lex was relieved, but kept it to himself. &quot;Why did you make the love comment then?&quot; Clark frowned ever so slightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lana says she is, Chloe I mean. But she's only been dating the guy for two weeks. You can't fall in love with someone in just two weeks,&quot; Clark protested. Lex chuckled and sipped his coffee.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can fall in love right away Clark. There's even a term for it,&quot; Lex responded. Clark sighed and leaned his cheek against his propped up fist.<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess,&quot; Clark said. &quot;It would explain why Chloe hasn't had a lot of time for her friends lately.&quot; Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;New relationships have a tendency to do that,&quot; Lex said. &quot;Eventually she'll grow bored with him and you'll get your friend back.&quot; Lex knew that no one would be able to compete for Chloe's attentions if he ever chose to toss his hat in the ring, but he wasn't ready to do that. 'Maybe after she breaks up with this new guy,' Lex mused. Clark smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;You sound pretty sure of that,&quot; he observed, snapping Lex out of his thoughts. &quot;But what if she doesn't get bored with him? Maybe she really likes him and will end up marrying him and--&quot; Clark stopped talking when Lex choked a little on his coffee. &quot;Are you okay?&quot; Lex nodded and wiped his mouth with a napkin.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm fine,&quot; Lex said, trying to cover up the fact that he was shocked at Clark's thoughts. Surely Chloe couldn't care that much about a boy, a high school boy at that, whom she had only been dating for a couple weeks. &quot;I doubt that's the case with Chloe, Clark. She's intelligent and witty, and regardless of how smart or good looking her new boyfriend is, the odds are he's not on her level of mental capacity. When she realizes that, she'll tire of him and move on to find someone more worthy of her.&quot; Clark's eyes widened.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow,&quot; Clark said. &quot;Better not let Luke catch you saying that stuff.&quot; Lex creased his brow.<br>
<br>
&quot;Luke?&quot; Lex repeated. It was one thing to have a nameless, faceless boy as competition, but naming him put a new spin on things. It made Lex feel slightly unsettled for some reason.<br>
<br>
&quot;Chloe's new boyfriend,&quot; Clark answered. &quot;And he is smart, he's an honor student.&quot; Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;But she just recently noticed him,&quot; Lex said. &quot;Which means that he can't be that spectacular.&quot; Clark laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, he just moved here from Coast City,&quot; Clark said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why?&quot; Lex asked, his tone indicating that most people would have much preferred Coast City to Smallville. Clark smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey! Smallville's not that bad!&quot; Clark argued. Lex laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you say so,&quot; Chloe's feminine voice said from beside the table. Lex and Clark both looked up at her. &quot;Mind if I join you?&quot; She asked, already sitting herself down next to Clark. &quot;So what are you guys talking about?&quot; Clark smiled, but didn't answer. Lex, on the other hand, had no problem with the subject they had just been discussing.<br>
<br>
&quot;You actually,&quot; Lex said. Chloe raised her eyebrows in surprise.<br>
<br>
&quot;My name was brought up in a discussion that included 'Smallville's not that bad'? I think I should be insulted,&quot; she responded. Clark and Lex both chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's not like that Chlo,&quot; Clark said. &quot;We were talking about you and Luke, and how Luke just moved here from Coast City.&quot; Chloe smiled and sipped her coffee.<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess I can forgive you then,&quot; she said. Clark rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gee thanks,&quot; he said sarcastically. Chloe gave a half laugh and then caught the clock on the wall with her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Crap! Is that the right time?&quot; She asked to nobody in particular. Chloe looked down at her watch, only to see that it had stopped. &quot;Ugh! Stupid watch,&quot; she mumbled. Chloe got up out of her chair and Clark frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's wrong?&quot; He asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have to meet Luke in like ten minutes and I'm going to be late,&quot; she said with a sigh.<br>
<br>
&quot;But you just got here,&quot; Clark complained. She gave him a compensatory smile and grabbed her bag. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sure you'll find a way to compensate with your driving speed Miss Sullivan,&quot; he quipped. Chloe gave a rather unladylike snort.<br>
<br>
&quot;If I was driving, then I wouldn't be late,&quot; she said. &quot;But I have no car today, and therefore, I'm hoofing it.&quot; Chloe waved at Clark and Lex as she started to walk away. &quot;Bye.&quot; Lana waved to her after she reached the front door and she gave her a smile and a wave. Lex frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I should have offered her a ride,&quot; he said. Clark gave him a strange look.<br>
<br>
&quot;She wouldn't have taken it,&quot; Clark said. Lex tilted his head at the observation, not realizing that he had said what he thought out loud.<br>
<br>
&quot;Probably not,&quot; he agreed. &quot;But it wasn't very chivalrous of me not to even offer.&quot; The comment earned a full laugh from Clark.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't think she sees you as chivalrous, and even if she did, I don't think Luke would be very happy seeing you give his girlfriend a ride,&quot; Clark said. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;The jealous type is he?&quot; Lex asked in a way that it didn't sound like a question. 'If she doesn't end up dumping him, I can use that to my advantage,' he thought. Clark shrugged.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't know,&quot; Clark admitted and then smiled. &quot;But if I was going out with her and I saw you giving her a ride--&quot; Clark trailed off.<br>
<br>
&quot;Point taken.&quot;<br>
