<br>
&quot;Luke I presume?&quot; Lex commented to Clark. Clark glanced back over to Lex and nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; he confirmed. &quot;She seems happy doesn't she?&quot; Clark observed. Lex arched an eyebrow at Clark's somewhat rueful tone, but decided not to comment on it.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wonder why she came back,&quot; Lex thought aloud. Clark's eyebrows raised in surprise and pensiveness.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know,&quot; Clark admitted and casually looked around the place so Chloe wouldn't notice that he had been staring at them. &quot;It's not really the sort of place you take a date.&quot; Lex chuckled. &quot;What?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Isn't this where you and Lana spend the majority of your time together?&quot; Lex asked. Clark blushed.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's not what I meant,&quot; Clark argued. Lex smirked. Chloe and Luke placed their order at the counter and then worked their way over to Clark and Lex's table. Lex noticed that Chloe was the only one with a cup of coffee in her hands. He smiled inwardly, or so he thought. Chloe smiled brightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you smirking about?&quot; She asked Lex. Luke laughed at the surprised expression that splayed across Lex's features, and Lex quickly covered his reaction.<br>
<br>
&quot;Back so soon Miss Sullivan?&quot; Lex asked, purposefully ignoring the fact that Luke was standing right next to her. &quot;Can't stay away from me?&quot; He teased. Chloe rolled her eyes and sat down next to Clark. Luke pulled another chair to the table so he could sit next to Chloe.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, that's it,&quot; she said sarcastically.<br>
<br>
&quot;I thought you said you were going to be late to meet your boyfriend,&quot; Lex said.<br>
<br>
&quot;She was late,&quot; Luke answered. He tried to hide his displeasure at the fact that Lex was intentionally ignoring his presence. Chalk it up to being an only child, but Luke wasn't used to being ignored. He grinned tightly. &quot;So I drove in this direction on the hunch that she would be near some caffeine. And what d'ya know? I was right.&quot; Chloe slapped the back of her hand against his chest playfully and Luke's grin turned into a smile. Lex's tongue rested itself in the corner of his mouth and he narrowed his eyes a little when Luke and Chloe leaned closer to each other. Watching their lips about to connect, Lex decided to take action. He cleared his throat and Chloe and Luke pulled away from their almost-kiss.<br>
<br>
&quot;We haven't been properly introduced,&quot; Lex said and extended his hand. &quot;Lex Luthor.&quot; Luke squared his jaw slightly and gave him a weary and untrusting look, but it wasn't because of the Luthor name, or because of the fact that Lex hadn't been acknowledging his existence just moments before. Luke noticed the way Lex had been looking at Chloe when they first came into the building, and he didn't like it. And now, Lex was interrupting a 'moment' between him and Chloe. Despite his reservations, Luke extended his hand as well and shook Lex's.<br>
<br>
&quot;Luke Atherton,&quot; Luke answered. Lex gave a curt nod and a partial smirk.<br>
<br>
&quot;So you're Luke,&quot; Lex said in an observational tone. &quot;Clark tells me that you hail from Coast City. What brings you to Smallville Mr. Atherton?&quot; Lex asked. Luke raised an eyebrow at the formality of using his last name, but ultimately decided that the young man in front of him must just have some sort of weird mental complex. After all, who wears a suit to get coffee on a late Saturday afternoon?<br>
<br>
&quot;My dad,&quot; Luke responded. Lex gave a curt nod and took a sip of his coffee.<br>
<br>
&quot;Job transfer?&quot; Lex asked. Luke shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; he answered. Lex noticed the strange look Luke got in his eyes. He seemed remorseful for some reason. Chloe gently touched Luke's arm and gave him a reassuring grin. &quot;My mother died a couple of months ago,&quot; Luke said in a choked, yet controlled voice. Lex's heart fell.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sorry,&quot; he replied.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's okay,&quot; Luke said, although his tone indicated that it wasn't alright at all. &quot;She was sick for a long time. I think she was just tired of being kept alive by machines.&quot; Lex inwardly cringed. He could relate to Luke's story all too well. Luke gazed at Chloe with a loving expression and grinned. He placed his hand on the hand she had resting on his arm. &quot;That's actually one of the things that Chloe and I have in common.&quot; Lex and Clark shared a confused look.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, my mom is still alive somewhere. But she's been gone for a long time and she's dead to me,&quot; Chloe said sadly. Lex was surprised at her sharp tone. Clark had told him about Chloe's mom deserting her and her dad and how upset she was by it, but he never pictured her as bitter about it, only heartbroken. Of course, that only meant that they had one more thing in common as well. He wondered if Chloe had ever considered that. Regardless, the atmosphere around their table had taken on a considerably sour tone, and it was time to change the topic. Lex turned his full attention on Chloe.<br>
<br>
&quot;Clark tells me that you two have only been dating for a couple of weeks,&quot; Lex said bluntly. &quot;How did you meet?&quot; Luke smirked at Lex's obvious attempt to derail his status in front of Chloe. Lex narrowed his eyes slightly at the smirk. He knew that look, that exact smirk, but he still couldn't place the boy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Chloe had to interview me for the school paper,&quot; Luke answered nonchalantly. &quot;We started talking and realized that we have a lot in common.&quot; Lex gave him a polite grin, but had to stifle a groan when he saw the way Chloe was looking at Luke.<br>
<br>
'She thinks she's in love with him,' Lex thought to himself. 'This could be more difficult than I thought.' Although he had no intention of actively pursuing Chloe immediately, he didn't want Luke to ruin his chances in the long run.<br>
<br>
&quot;Really?&quot; Lex asked with a mock interested inflection in his voice. &quot;Such as?&quot; Chloe shot Lex a look and he grinned at her over his mug of coffee. She leaned forward on her arms.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow,&quot; she said sarcastically. &quot;Why so interested in my life all of a sudden?&quot; Clark cringed at her tone and looked at Lex apologetically. Her comment didn't seem to phase Lex at all; in fact it seemed to only fuel the banter fire the two had been exchanging for a while now. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just honing my investigative skills,&quot; he replied. Chloe laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gunning for my future position at The Daily Planet?&quot; She teased. Lex smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sadly no,&quot; he responded. &quot;But I think I could get hired on at The Inquisitor.&quot; Chloe smiled wider.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course you could,&quot; she said. &quot;You own it.&quot; Luke looked back and forth between the two with some suspicion. The way they used their wordplay was entirely too friendly. It could have been construed as flirting if they were talking about anything else. Luke decided to let it slide.<br>
<br>
Chloe had been honest with him, he was sure of that. No other girl he knew would admit to having a failed crush on her best friend, or being a 'mutant magnet' of sorts. But the most she had mentioned about Lex Luthor was that he basically owned the town, which he had already figured out for himself, and that he was a friend of Clark's. He trusted Chloe. Luke smiled to himself. Even if Lex did like Chloe, Luke surmised that he was really no competition for him. And he was going to make sure of it.<br>
