<br>
&quot;Is my father in?&quot; Lex asked. The man nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes sir,&quot; the butler answered. &quot;But he has company and has asked not to be disturbed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What company?&quot; Lex asked. His mind automatically went to one of his father's ex gold digging flings, which he really had no patience for dealing with right now.<br>
<br>
&quot;His first name is Michael,&quot; the man responded. &quot;He didn't give a last name, but your father recognized his voice and immediately invited him into his study.&quot; Lex gave a curt nod.<br>
<br>
'Interesting,' Lex thought. 'But it would be more interesting if I knew what he was up to.'<br>
<br>
&quot;He did ask not to be disturbed,&quot; the butler reminded him in a half warning voice. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;If he wants privacy, he should move back to Metropolis,&quot; Lex responded. The butler said nothing, but shook his head slightly in disapproval and walked away from him. Lex began walking in the direction of his father's study. When he was a few doors away, he could hear raised voices. He neared the closed door of the study so he could hear what they were saying.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's MY son!&quot; A man's voice exclaimed in anger. Lex presumed that this was the 'Michael' that his butler referred to.<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; Lionel sneered. &quot;He's *my* son.&quot; Lionel's voice was in a lower volume than Michael's, but Lex could tell from his tone that he was seething. There was a pause and Lex backed away from the door a couple of steps in case the other man decided to come storming out of it.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can't do this,&quot; Michael said. Lex noted that it sounded like he was pleading with his father, and he had to stifle a snort at what the consequences would be.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can, and I will,&quot; Lionel said. Lex heard him sigh and he creased his brow. Surely Lionel wasn't going to give in? &quot;He doesn't know his biological father the way he should, a fact for which I feel deeply ashamed. With or without your blessing, I'm going to set things right.&quot; Lex frowned at this.<br>
<br>
'Biological father?' Lex thought. The first thought that came to mind was that Lionel had sired illegitimate offspring, but it wouldn't be the first time, and his father showed no interest in getting to know them before. 'What if they're talking about me?' He thought. He realized that he hadn't been told everything there was to know about his mother Lillian. He only had his own memories of her, and what various people had told him. He couldn't chastise her for having an affair of her own, certainly not with Lionel as her husband. Lex's mind was reeling. Could it be true? He was snapped out of his thoughts when his father and Michael started speaking again.<br>
<br>
&quot;As long as you know---&quot; Michael said.<br>
<br>
&quot;---Where you stand,&quot; Lionel finished and slightly paused before speaking again. &quot;I understand completely. Tomorrow then?&quot; Lex heard them say their gruff goodbyes and he leaned against the wall by the door. Michael exited and Lex nodded at him, carefully taking in his appearance. Michael was a little taller than he was. He had dark auburn hair that was cut short, he was handsome, and he was wearing well tailored clothes. Lex's eyebrows rose at the possibility that he was seeing his real father for the first time. He watched the man walk away and then he entered his father's study.<br>
<br>
