'Sympathy for the man who wants to steal my girlfriend away from me,' Luke thought. 'I must be going crazy.'<br>
<br>
&quot;Lex is right,&quot; Luke said, pushing himself off of the chair. He was steadier on his feet now than he had been, and was trying to sound sure of himself. If there was one thing he remembered about being around Lionel, it was that he appreciated self-confidence. &quot;I'm not feeling well, and I wouldn't want to get you sick.&quot; 'Not that it's contagious,' Luke thought to himself. Lionel grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;How thoughtful,&quot; he responded. &quot;But quite unnecessary. You're here to have breakfast with me. Just cough in the other direction.&quot; He turned around and started to tap his cane as he walked. Luke watched him leave in disbelief. He turned to his dad for an explanation, but Michael simply took a deep breath and gave him an apologetic look. Lex came up behind him and slapped his hand on his back.<br>
<br>
&quot;Welcome to the family,&quot; Lex said dryly.<br>
<br>
Luke and Michael followed Lionel and Lex as they walked toward the dining room. Luke decided to take the opportunity to mark his territory, so to speak, but it wasn't about his surroundings. He tilted his head toward Michael.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can see why this place creeps Chloe out,&quot; he said in a low voice that was just loud enough for Lex to hear. Lex squared his jaw and silently told himself that he wouldn't let Luke play mind games with him about Chloe. Obviously Luke had figured out that Lex liked her, and that was definitely to his advantage rather than Lex's. Lex kept walking straight ahead, but responded to Luke's comment.<br>
<br>
&quot;The fact that she was pushed out a window from the second floor probably has something to do with it,&quot; Lex said coolly. Luke's eyebrows rose in surprise. Chloe hadn't told him that. Why had Chloe not told him that?<br>
<br>
&quot;Who pushed her?&quot; Luke asked accusingly. Lex smirked and then turned around to face Luke, but continued to walk only now in a backwards motion.<br>
<br>
&quot;We were in the middle of an interview when some burglars broke in. In their haste to get away, one of them pushed her out the window,&quot; Lex said and then turned back around. &quot;She didn't tell you?&quot; Lex jabbed over his shoulder.<br>
<br>
To an outsider, the conversation would have seemed a little on the stranger side of normal, but normal none the less. They had a mutual friend whom they were discussing and that was it. To someone who knew one or the other's mannerisms though, it was a completely different play on words. Michael took a deep breath. He really didn't want to get in the middle of this, but if he stuck by Luke, then he had a better chance of not losing him to Lionel's darker influence. They reached the dining room right as he asked the question and Lex proceeded to sit down. Lionel insisted that his sons sit on either side of him with himself positioned at the head of the table. Michael sat next to Luke on the opposite side.<br>
<br>
&quot;You know Luke's girlfriend?&quot; Michael asked Lex. Lex was about to answer him when Lionel grinned and butted into the conversation.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have a girlfriend Lucas?&quot; Lionel queried. Luke was glad that Lionel couldn't see him wince when he called him by his full first name. Nobody except Lionel did that, and the way he made it sound was like he wasn't accepting of who Luke was as a person, but rather who he wanted him to be. Luke cleared his throat and took a sip from the glass of water in front of him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes sir,&quot; he answered.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir? My, that's formal,&quot; Lionel commented. &quot;You can call me father if you'd like.&quot; Lex winced at that one. Lionel never pulled any punches. The man who raised the boy was sitting at the same table and Lionel had the audacity to make a comment like that. Luke glared at his biological father, again grateful that he had lost his sight.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'd rather not,&quot; Luke retorted. A strange expression crossed over Lionel's face, one of remorse or regret, but it was gone just as soon as it arrived, and he replaced it with a smug grin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course,&quot; Lionel said. &quot;All things in time.&quot; Lex glanced at Luke and gave him a sympathetic look. Despite the fact that Lex liked Chloe, Luke found himself wanting to side with him. It was transparent that Lex and Lionel were at odds about several things that had gone on between them in their lives, and Luke didn't want to be on the team that would make intentionally vicious comments with no regard to people's feelings. Luke found himself wondering if this brother thing wasn't such a bad situation after all. Maybe he could even convince Lex to give up his crush on Chloe. That was really the only thing standing in the way of them becoming friends. That, and Lionel.<br>
