<br>
&quot;You said that you had a girlfriend Lucas?&quot; Lionel asked. Lex looked up from his plate to Luke.<br>
<br>
'This ought to be good,' Lex thought.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's her name?&quot; Lionel asked. &quot;Tell me about her.&quot; Luke swallowed the bite of food he had been chewing and smiled.<br>
<br>
'Poor guy doesn't know what he's in for,' Lex thought. 'But it should definitely prove to be entertaining.'<br>
<br>
&quot;Her name is Chloe,&quot; Luke answered. He was about to say more when Lionel cut him off.<br>
<br>
&quot;And does Chloe have a last name?&quot; Lionel asked. Luke rolled his eyes. Lex grinned. If his father was trying to win Luke over, he was doing a horrible job of it. Luke's next statement caught Lex completely off guard.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hmm, I think so,&quot; Luke said sarcastically. &quot;But she's considering dropping it and just going by her first name like a lot of actresses do.&quot; Lex coughed on the orange juice he was drinking and a little of it flew from his mouth. He looked at Luke, who had a giant smile across his face. Luke's smile seemed to be contagious, as one spread on Lex's own lips as well. Lionel, however, wasn't amused. The serious expression on his face caused Luke to burst out in laughter and Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;I see,&quot; Lionel said. &quot;You were joking.&quot; He said it so dryly that it made Luke cringe. &quot;Well, good to know that you feel comfortable enough around me to do so. Now, what's her last name?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sullivan,&quot; Luke replied. &quot;But I don't see why it matters, it's not like you know her.&quot; He mumbled the last part and shoved some eggs into his mouth. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, he does,&quot; Lex said. &quot;Her father is the plant manager.&quot; Lionel's eyebrows rose.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gabe Sullivan's daughter?&quot; He asked. Lionel shook his head in disapproval. &quot;She's only dating you for your money; you'll have to break things off with her.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What money?&quot; Luke scoffed.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're a Luthor son, you need to be wary of women who will only date you to serve their own advancement in this world,&quot; Lionel said in a completely serious voice. Luke smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I didn't know that you were my biological father until like an hour ago,&quot; Luke reminded him. &quot;And Chloe doesn't even know yet, so she's obviously not dating me because of that.&quot; Lionel looked thoughtful.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hmm, a valid argument,&quot; Lionel conceded. &quot;But just imagine how she'll react when she does find out. No doubt she'll want you to take her shopping or something.&quot; Luke frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, she'll probably think about dumping me,&quot; he said with a completely straight face. Lex tried to hide the grin that was forming on his lips.<br>
<br>
'I'll have to tell her for you,' Lex mused to himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;I seriously doubt that. I would think that being a Luthor would only endear you to her more,&quot; Lionel said and then felt around until he reached his cup of coffee. Luke shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;You don't know her,&quot; he objected. &quot;She's not like that.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;All women are like that,&quot; Lionel retorted.<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you have against Chloe?&quot; Luke asked a little angrily. His temper was starting to rise and having breakfast with this jerk who turned out to be related to him wasn't helping. Lex chuckled and looked at Luke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing,&quot; Lex said to him. &quot;That's the problem.&quot; Luke looked confused.<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you mean?&quot; Luke asked. Lex glanced at his father and took a deep breath before explaining the situation to Luke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Last year, at some horrible company function, he had a little too much to drink. Chloe was there because of Gabe, and dear old dad started to hit on her,&quot; Lex said. A smirk etched itself onto Lex's face as he turned to look at Lionel. &quot;She called you a 'lecherous old man' if my memory serves me correctly. And I'm fairly certain she would have slapped you if her father hadn't gotten to her in time.&quot; Luke smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, that sounds like her,&quot; he said. Lionel's eyes grew wide.<br>
<br>
&quot;That was Chloe Sullivan?&quot; Lionel asked. &quot;Goodness, she's lovely.&quot; Luke and Lex both frowned. &quot;And quite spirited. I'm surprised you were able to get her to go out with you in the first place.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Gee thanks,&quot; Luke said sarcastically.<br>
<br>
&quot;That didn't come out the way I meant it,&quot; Lionel said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Right,&quot; Lex said. &quot;The way he meant it was if he, in an inebriated state, couldn't get her to pay attention to his clumsy advances, then surely no other man would be able to woo her.&quot; Luke laughed and Lionel let out an aggravated sigh.<br>
<br>
&quot;And here I thought I would be thankful if you two ended up getting along,&quot; Lionel said. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Be careful what you wish for,&quot; he responded.<br>
<br>
Breakfast ended rather uneventfully and Lionel made Luke promise to come to see him again soon. After Lionel left to go to his study, Lex walked Luke and Michael to the front door. His father may have forgotten his manners, if he had them to begin with, but Lex hadn't.<br>
<br>
&quot;So,&quot; Luke said.<br>
<br>
&quot;So,&quot; Lex repeated. There was a slight pause and Lex frowned. &quot;Are you going to tell Chloe?&quot; Luke arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;If I don't, you will,&quot; Luke said bluntly. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Glad to know we're on the same page,&quot; he replied. Luke gave a curt nod and turned to open the door. He opened it and his dad stepped ahead of him onto the porch. Luke swung around once more to look at Lex.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, I almost forgot,&quot; Luke said. He turned to look at Michael quickly and asked him to wait for him at the car. Michael left and Luke looked back at Lex. &quot;I was hoping you could decipher something Chloe said for me.&quot; Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can try, but I should warn you that I'm not completely fluent in Chloe's language,&quot; Lex kidded. Luke nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;She said something about going to Metropolis just to spite you. You wouldn't happen to know what she meant by that would you?&quot; Luke asked. Lex pursed his lips.<br>
<br>
&quot;Was she serious?&quot; He asked. Luke shrugged.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hard to say,&quot; Luke admitted. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;I wouldn't worry about it,&quot; Lex said. &quot;If she was serious, she would be doing it to spite me, not you.&quot; Luke grinned too.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good point,&quot; he agreed. &quot;Of course it might help if I knew what you two had been talking about.&quot; He arched a suspicious eyebrow at Lex and Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sure it would,&quot; Lex responded cryptically. Luke resisted an eye roll. Lex had been pretty good about siding with him during breakfast, and it could very well be that he was just being paranoid about the situation since he and Chloe hadn't been dating that long.<br>
<br>
&quot;I should go, Dad's waiting for me,&quot; Luke finally said. Lex nodded and extended a hand for him to shake.<br>
<br>
&quot;Luke,&quot; Lex said. Luke smiled at the use of his first name.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lex,&quot; he said and shook his hand. Luke turned and walked out the door. Lex watched Luke until he got to the car and then he shut the door. Lex wondered if Chloe would actually go to Metropolis to flirt with a bouncer and go dancing just to make him angry.<br>
<br>
'Of course she would,' Lex thought. The corners of his mouth curled upward. He couldn't help but think that the beginning of the end of her relationship with Luke would be coming soon. He looked forward to that day.<br>
