<br>
&quot;That's great news,&quot; Chloe said. &quot;I guess.&quot; She was still a little dazed from having him wake her up and start regaling his tale of what happened at breakfast. &quot;How do you feel about it?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hard to say,&quot; Luke admitted. He wished that she had chosen the couch to sit down on so he could sit next to her, but it probably wouldn't be the appropriate time to start kissing her anyway. &quot;How do you feel about it?&quot; Chloe looked at him quizzically.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, it doesn't really affect me Luke, not like it affects you,&quot; she answered. &quot;You're the one whose life has just taken a major turn.&quot; Luke nodded. &quot;Have you told anybody else?&quot; Luke shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Came straight over after I dropped my dad off at home,&quot; he said. Chloe kept a straight face and he tilted his head at her. &quot;He's still my dad Chlo,&quot; Luke misinterpreted her expression and tried to explain. &quot;He's the one who raised me, the one who was always there for me. This new information doesn't change that.&quot; She nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know,&quot; she said. He arched an eyebrow and she took a deep breath. &quot;It's just---&quot; she paused while trying to think of a delicate way to phrase what she needed to say. &quot;Some things run genetically in families, and I don't want you to change.&quot; Luke frowned.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're friends with Lex,&quot; he pointed out. &quot;I don't see how it's any different.&quot; Chloe shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm acquaintances with Lex, not friends,&quot; she corrected. &quot;And I know that he's had a pretty awful life in spots.&quot; Luke's look told her to continue. &quot;I also know that Lionel Luthor is the closest thing to Satan that Smallville will probably ever see.&quot; An expression of understanding passed over Luke's face.<br>
<br>
&quot;And you're worried because, technically, I'm his spawn,&quot; Luke said. Chloe smiled apologetically.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm sorry,&quot; she said. &quot;It sounds ridiculous. I'm just having trouble shaking the feeling that Lionel Luthor is going to be a negative influence on you.&quot; He smiled and walked over to her, holding out his hand to help her out of the chair.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then you'll balance it out,&quot; he said comfortingly. They kissed and Chloe smiled when they pulled apart from each other. Her smile fell when she noticed the serious expression on Luke's face. &quot;May I ask you a question?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow,&quot; she teased. &quot;Correct grammar and everything.&quot; Luke smiled. &quot;Sure, go ahead,&quot; Chloe said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why are you willing to forgive Lex for his genetic makeup but not me?&quot; He asked with a tinge of jealousy that Chloe missed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't take it personally,&quot; she said. &quot;I've just known him longer. I know how much he's been through to try and become a person that you want to be friends with, someone who looks out for the people he cares for and not just himself.&quot; Luke furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
&quot;And you don't think I'm like that?&quot; He asked in a hurt voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think you've been like that from the start, but it's a different story when you have to overcome natural selfish tendencies because of the way you were raised,&quot; she said. Luke nodded. That made sense. Chloe got a sparkle in her eye. &quot;You almost sound like you're jealous.&quot; Luke frowned and tightened the grip of his hands on her waist.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe I am,&quot; Luke replied, not completely admitting to it.<br>
<br>
&quot;You shouldn't be,&quot; Chloe said. &quot;I'm sure that you'll end up having a much deeper friendship with your brother than I ever will.&quot; Luke tried to hold back his surprise at her comment. She thought that he was jealous because she was trying to be 'friends' with Lex?<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess you're right,&quot; Luke said. Chloe smiled again.<br>
<br>
&quot;So I don't suppose I could get an interview with the newest Luthor?&quot; She asked. Luke chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;You really do have a one track mind don't you?&quot; He asked. Her smile didn't diminish.<br>
<br>
&quot;Or maybe a joint interview with you and Lex?&quot; She asked. Chloe got a distinctive sparkle in her eyes as she imagined the possible headlines. Luke opened his mouth to speak, but she cut him off. &quot;Ooh, that would be great.&quot; Luke arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yeah, really great,&quot; he said sarcastically. &quot;Considering how well your other interview attempts with Lex have gone.&quot; Chloe wouldn't be defeated that easily though. She stepped away from Luke and brushed off the comment.<br>
<br>
&quot;You'll be there too this time, that can only bring good luck,&quot; she said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Or bad luck,&quot; Luke mumbled. Chloe shot him a questioning look.<br>
<br>
&quot;What's that supposed to mean?&quot; She asked. Luke ran a hand through his hair and faked a smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing,&quot; he lied. He couldn't very well tell her that he had no desire to watch Lex flirt with her for the duration of the interview; because he knew that she would just deny it and say that he was being paranoid and ridiculous.<br>
<br>
&quot;Uh huh,&quot; Chloe said as she crossed her arms. Luke sighed and shook his head at her. He gave her his best smile, but she still looked unconvinced.<br>
<br>
'To tell her or not to tell her? That is the question,' Luke thought. Against his better judgment, he decided to opt for the first.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think he likes you,&quot; Luke finally said. Chloe stared at him blankly for a moment and then smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Everybody likes me,&quot; she joked. &quot;Can you be more specific?&quot; Luke chuckled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lex,&quot; he answered. Chloe's smile didn't fall.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course he likes me Luke, I'm his best verbal sparring partner,&quot; she said. Luke rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's not what I meant,&quot; he said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fine,&quot; Chloe said. &quot;What did you mean?&quot; Luke shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;He *likes* you,&quot; Luke clarified. Chloe smiled and tried to hold back her laughter, but it didn't work and she started laughing hysterically.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, okay,&quot; she said through her laughter. &quot;Whatever you say honey.&quot; The corners of Luke's mouth started to curl upward. Chloe's laughter was contagious.<br>
<br>
&quot;You don't believe me?&quot; He asked. Chloe shook her head and held her stomach as she started laughing harder. &quot;I'm not sure whether that's a good thing or not,&quot; Luke said to himself. Chloe's laughter tapered off and she gave Luke a halfway sympathetic look.<br>
<br>
&quot;You were serious?&quot; She asked in disbelief. He stared at her and she shook her head. &quot;O-kay. What makes you think that?&quot; She asked. Luke shrugged and went to sit down again.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can just tell,&quot; he said. Chloe smiled and went to sit down next to him. She rested her head on his shoulder and he grinned down at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Would it help if I said you were completely off base?&quot; She asked. Despite his frustration with the situation, Luke found himself laughing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yeah,&quot; he said sarcastically. &quot;That's a big help.&quot; She kissed his cheek and he turned his face to kiss her properly.<br>
<br>
&quot;This isn't going to be a problem is it?&quot; Chloe asked. &quot;Because despite what I said earlier, I really would like to be friends with Lex, and I want you to get to know your brother.&quot; Luke rubbed his face with his hands and faked a grin.<br>
<br>
&quot;No,&quot; he lied. &quot;You're probably right. I was probably reading too much into the situation and he only likes you as a friend.&quot; Chloe's face brightened.<br>
<br>
&quot;Exactly,&quot; she said. Chloe snuggled up to him and their mouths were millimeters apart. &quot;Now where were we?&quot;<br>
