<br>
&quot;I can't believe he actually agreed to this,&quot; she said. Luke frowned. He didn't find it hard to believe at all.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course he did,&quot; Luke mumbled under his breath. Chloe arched an eyebrow at him, but decided to say nothing. She didn't want to have this fight again. She didn't understand how he could be so paranoid about something that wasn't even the truth. Instead, she brought her mug up to her lips and took a sip of her coffee, pretending that she hadn't heard his comment. Luke smiled at her reaction and she grinned back at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You two look cozy,&quot; Lex said as he suddenly appeared at their table. Chloe smiled brightly at him and Luke gave him a polite nod.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lex,&quot; Luke greeted and held out a hand. Lex shook it and then sat down across from Chloe. Luke glared at him slightly, but said nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Miss Sullivan,&quot; Lex said. Chloe's smile seemed to grow wider.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mr. Luthor,&quot; she replied. Lex was grinning and Luke felt incredibly uncomfortable with the immediate chemistry the two seemed to have. He wondered if Chloe noticed it. He knew Lex did. A waitress came by the table and Lex placed his order. He turned back to look at Chloe.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's been a while since I've seen you Chloe,&quot; Lex said in a casual manner. Chloe nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know,&quot; she said. &quot;I've been pretty busy lately.&quot; Lex cast a glance at Luke through the corner of his eye. There was no doubt in his mind that Luke had been trying to keep Chloe busy so she wouldn't have time to run into him or her other friends. Clark had told him as much.<br>
<br>
&quot;The life of a reporter I suppose,&quot; Lex said. Chloe smiled again and tucked some hair behind her ear.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; Chloe agreed. &quot;So what have you been up to?&quot; Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't realize that the interview had started already,&quot; he replied. She laughed.<br>
<br>
&quot;It hasn't,&quot; she said. &quot;I was trying to be polite.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah. So you don't really care how I've been spending my time?&quot; Lex asked. Chloe leaned forward a little.<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't say that,&quot; she said. Lex smiled and Luke groaned. Lex and Chloe both looked over at him questioningly. The second she saw the expression on his face, she knew what Luke was thinking. She tilted her head at him. &quot;Please don't start this again,&quot; she pleaded in a half hushed voice. Luke grumbled and crossed his arms. Lex looked at him suspiciously. The only reason he hadn't interfered in their relationship yet was because he had actually grown to like his brother, and he figured that the boy had enough common sense to treat Chloe correctly. Lex was now wondering if that wasn't a big mistake on his part.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't start what?&quot; Lex asked sternly. His question was directed at Luke, but Chloe answered it. She sat up straight in her chair with a determined look on her face.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're settling this right now,&quot; she told Luke. Lex looked over at her and arched an eyebrow. She smiled at him. &quot;Luke has a crazy idea in his head-- -&quot; Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just one?&quot; Lex interrupted. Chloe rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;He thinks that you like me,&quot; she continued. Lex furrowed his brow and then stared blankly at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Have I given you any indication that I don't like you Chloe?&quot; He asked. A soft smile spread across her lips and she shook her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not as a friend,&quot; she answered. &quot;He thinks that you *like* me.&quot; Lex gave a knowing look to Luke, who squared his jaw.<br>
<br>
&quot;I see,&quot; Lex said dryly. Chloe smiled smugly.<br>
<br>
