<br>
&quot;You know, the usual speech when it comes to anyone who I've dated. I don't trust him, something's going on, you should be careful,&quot; she rattled off. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's your friend Chloe, he's just trying to look out for you,&quot; he said.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know,&quot; Chloe responded. &quot;I just --- I was hoping that this time he was wrong. You know?&quot; Lex pursed his lips and nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know,&quot; he said as he pulled the car up into her driveway. She let out a small gasp when she misread the expression on his face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh Lex, I'm so sorry,&quot; she said. &quot;I didn't mean anything by that. It's still hard for me to remember that you two are related.&quot; Lex kept a stoic look on his face.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's okay Chloe,&quot; he said reassuringly. &quot;You're hurting as much as I am.&quot; He wondered if she believed that. It was only a partial lie. He wasn't hurting at all over the fact that Luke was going to be out of Chloe's life, but it did pain him to know that he had let it go on as long as it did. &quot;I'll walk you to your door,&quot; he said. &quot;I want to speak with your dad.&quot;<br>
