<br>
Chloe, he warned again. Do you know how much trouble you could get into at one of those places? Chloe sloughed off the comment.<br>
<br>
Would it make you feel better if I got you copies of the documents tonight?<br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
So you just dont want me to go dancing then, is that it?<br>
<br>
I just dont want you to get hurt, he corrected.<br>
<br>
You may not believe this, but I am capable of taking care of myself Lex. And even if I wasnt, theres nothing you can do about it.<br>
<br>
Not true. I could tell your dad.<br>
<br>
But you wont because you want the documents that prove that your dad is involved in illegal activities, she countered.<br>
<br>
Speaking of which, why havent you used that information for an article yet?<br>
<br>
Like I said, they werent exactly legally obtained, she said. But Im guessing that you would find a way around that. Lex nodded. So just be my friend and be happy for me. There was a lapse in the conversation as they tried to stare each other down. Lex squared his jaw and managed to force a grin onto his face.<br>
<br>
Youre right, he said. Youre young and you deserve to have some fun. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
Thank you, she said. Lex leaned back in his chair.<br>
<br>
So which clubs were you thinking about hitting? He asked as casually as he could.<br>
<br>
Just one actually. My friend Lucy knows the bouncer at Meridian.<br>
