<br>
Chloe, wait, he said. Chloe stilled and turned to look at him, but said nothing. Lex stood up, tightening his grip on her hand. Its not what you think. Chloe pulled her hand away from him and crossed her arms.<br>
<br>
Okay, so what do I think? She asked. Lex sighed as he stared down at her.<br>
<br>
You said Luke was right, but he wasnt.<br>
<br>
You just kissed me, Chloe argued. Lex stepped closer to her and moved his free hand around her waist. His head leaned toward her and for a second Chloe thought that he was going to kiss her again, but instead she felt his warm breath against her ear.<br>
<br>
We kissed each other, he corrected. Lex glanced at her face through the corner of his eye and saw that her eyes were closed. He took that as a good sign. Lex kissed the shell of her ear and peppered kisses across her cheek until he reached her lips. In one fluid movement, Chloes arms were wound around his neck and they were kissing passionately. Chloe pulled away from him to breathe and Lex rested his forehead against hers. Chloe?<br>
<br>
Hmm?<br>
<br>
Luke was right, Lex whispered. Chloe gave a slight nod of her head.<br>
<br>
I know, she replied in a hushed voice.<br>
<br>
That doesnt excuse the way he treated you, he said.<br>
<br>
I know, she said again. Lex brought his mouth to hers and gave her a sweet, almost chaste kiss. Chloe smiled to herself and Lex raised an eyebrow. So I guess this means you dont want me to get back together with him, huh? Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
I didnt want you to be with him in the first place, he responded and kissed her again. They didnt notice the eyes boring a hole through them from the outside window. Luke stood there with his hands clenched at his sides, ready to kill his brother for stealing Chloe away from him. He took a deep breath and remembered his conversation with Lionel. He needed to show restraint over his emotions if he was ever going to get her back. Luke took out his cell phone and hit a speed dial number.<br>
<br>
Luthor, Lionel answered.<br>
<br>
You said you were going to help, so help, Luke spat angrily into the phone.<br>
<br>
Lucas, Lionel greeted. You sound upset.<br>
<br>
Hes kissing her! Do something! Luke growled. Lionel arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
Hes kissing her? Ah, this must have something to do with that Sullivan girl, he mused aloud. I thought you said she wasnt interested in him, Lionel questioned. Luke sighed and ran a hand through his hair.<br>
<br>
Just do something, he pleaded. Im never going to get her back if Lex keeps on her like this.<br>
<br>
Calm down son. Things will be taken care of, Lionel said and hung up the phone. He seemed thoughtful before picking up the phone again. He had originally agreed to help Lucas with the situation to get closer to his son and to add fuel to the fire of antagonism that he and Lex had going, but now Lucas sounded desperate. Weak. Lionel fingered the phones keypad until he managed to dial the number in his memory. He held the phone up to his ear and waiting for an answer. Lex pulled away from Chloe when his cell phone started ringing. He frowned as he checked who it was and answered it.<br>
<br>
Luthor, Lex answered.<br>
<br>
Funny, I thought that was my line, Lionel said dryly.<br>
<br>
What do you want Dad? Lex asked. Chloes eyes grew a little wider and she moved to get her purse as if to leave. Lex stopped her and shook his head. Stay, he mouthed.<br>
<br>
Now is that any way to greet your father? Lionel asked with a sneer. Especially when I have news thats relevant to your situation.<br>
<br>
And what situation would that be? Lex asked as he began to lose his patience.<br>
<br>
Were you aware that you have an audience? Lionel asked cryptically.<br>
<br>
Pardon?<br>
<br>
Your brother just called. Hes rather upset about you kissing his girlfriend, Lionel explained.<br>
<br>
Shes not his ---, Lex trailed off when he realized what his dad was saying. He looked around the Talon, but only a few other people were there and Luke wasnt one of them. Chloe looked at him quizzically and he frowned. Lex spotted Luke outside of the building and shut off his phone without saying goodbye or acknowledging his father any further. Lukes eyes met his and Luke walked to the front door. Chloe followed Lexs gaze to the front door and felt her stomach sink when she saw Luke walk in. Lex placed a reassuring hand on Chloes back. Its okay, he whispered toward her. Chloe shook her head.<br>
<br>
I should go, she said in a half-choked voice. Luke stalked toward them, his eyes on Lex the entire time.<br>
<br>
Get away from her, Luke said. He was amazed at how calm his voice sounded. Steady, yet it carried the underlying threatening tone. Ive become a Luthor, he thought to himself. He wasnt the only one. The one thought that passed through Lexs mind was how much Luke had managed to sound like their father at that exact moment. Luke glanced at Chloe. Do you see now? He wanted you for himself all along. Chloe closed her eyes and took in a deep breath. She had never wanted to run out of a room screaming so much in her entire life, but she knew the problem was never going to get any better until she confronted it. Unfortunately, that didnt make what she had to do any easier.<br>
<br>
Luke, stop it, she said. Luke furrowed his brow in confusion. Were not going out anymore, remember?<br>
<br>
So, what? Youre just going to let him seduce you into a rebound relationship? Luke asked. He shook his head and took a step toward her. It wont be like that Chloe. Hes not going to let you go.<br>
<br>
That sounds familiar, Lex mumbled under his breath.<br>
<br>
Im her *friend* Lex, Luke argued. I have every right to be concerned about her.<br>
<br>
And Im not her friend? Lex asked. Luke shook his head again and Lex looked at him in disbelief. I knew her before you did. Chloe inwardly groaned as the two men stepped closer toward each other.<br>
<br>
Theyre going to start circling like predators any minute now, she thought sarcastically. Her eyes widened when they actually did start circling each other. She cleared her throat loudly.<br>
<br>
You two obviously have some issues to work out that I have nothing to do with, so Im going to leave now, she said. Lexs face dropped. He hadnt meant to get into a fight with Luke, and certainly hadnt intended to ignore Chloe and her feelings in the process.<br>
<br>
Ill drive you home, he offered. Chloe shook her head and grabbed her oversized purse.<br>
<br>
Clark, Lana, and Pete should be getting out of the movie any minute now, she said. Ill grab a ride home with them. She looked back and forth between Lex and Luke. Give you some time to talk to your brother. She turned and walked toward the front door. Both Lex and Luke appeared stricken at the fact that she hadnt seen fit to stay and choose one of them over the other. Luke recovered first.<br>
<br>
Way to go Lex, Luke said sarcastically. Shes never going to talk to either one of us again. He walked out of the coffee shop and didnt see the smirk that crawled across Lexs mouth.<br>
<br>
Well, maybe not *you* Luke, Lex thought. But I know where shes going to be tomorrow night.<br>
