<br>
And here I thought your days of drunkenness and debauchery were behind you.<br>
<br>
Lex turned his head, and barely quelled the urge to clench his hands into fists.<br>
<br>
Lucas, he greeted dryly, drawing out his full name for effect.<br>
<br>
Alexander, Luke said.  He motioned toward the vehicle that Lex had just climbed out of.  A little high-end for this part of town, isnt it?  When I saw you leaving Smallville in a limo, I assumed that you would be going somewhere *nice* in Metropolis.<br>
<br>
Is there any particular reason youve taken to stalking me?<br>
<br>
Chloes harder to follow, Lucas admitted.  I dont think she came out of her house once this morning, not even for her usual Saturday morning coffee fix at the Talon.<br>
<br>
So, this is about Chloe?  Lex asked, already knowing the answer; but not wanting to let on that Chloe was probably already inside the club rather than back in Smallville.<br>
<br>
Limo, Luke said and motioned to the car with his head.  I thought you might have picked her up without my knowing about it, and were going to show her a night on the town or something.  Luke glanced at the club and then back at Lex.  But I can see that obviously isnt the case.  What happened?  Did she turn you down and none of your old dealers would make the trip out to the boons for you to wallow in self pity?<br>
<br>
Not that its any of your business, but Im meeting an old friend.  Speaking of which, Im running late, so if youll excuse me ---,<br>
<br>
Whatever.<br>
<br>
I can get you in if you dont believe me, Lex said coolly, only hoping that Luke wouldnt call him on his bluff.  Luke threw his head back and laughed.<br>
<br>
Pass.  If Im going to spend my Saturday night getting drunk in Metropolis, then its not going to be at a place where theyre likely to drug me and harvest my organs.<br>
<br>
Youve been reading too many tabloids, Lex said with a small grin.  And youre sure?  Because Id be more than happy to arrange it.<br>
<br>
Im sure you would, Luke said, turning slightly to head back to his own car.  Try not to show up on the front page of the papers tomorrow.  He flashed his brother a cocky smile.  Or do, you know, because it can only make me look better.<br>
<br>
