Thats not what I meant, he said.  Chloes lips formed a perfect o shape, her mind reeling back to the time in the Talon when he admitted to Luke being right about him liking her.  And Id like to think that if he had been treating you right, that I wouldnt have acted on my feelings; but I cant say Im sorry that ---<br>
<br>
Im glad you did, Chloe interrupted.  Lex looked surprised and she reached her hand out to him.  When he took it, she gave his hand a squeeze and continued.  You werent there, Lex.  Even if Luke *had* been a great guy the entire time we were going out, he would have snapped eventually.  Im glad you intervened and that hes going to get help now.  Lex gave her a pleased grin and nodded once.<br>
<br>
He is, he agreed.  Hes been admitted to the same mental health care facility that his mom is in.  And in addition to having the finest staff of professionals to treat him, they also have the best security --- hell never hurt you again, Chloe.  Chloe grinned.<br>
<br>
Why do I get the feeling that youll be hanging around me just to make sure? she teased. <br>
<br>
Oh, absolutely, Lex replied with a smug expression on his face.  Twenty-four-seven; whatever it takes to make you feel safe.  Chloe let laughter sweep through her body and Lex couldnt help but smile.  Only his Chloe could go through an ordeal like she had been through and still be able to laugh just a short while later.  <br>
<br>
Listen, Lex  about *us* --- she paused when she saw the expectant look on his face.  She could tell that he was worried about what she was going to say.  You were my first  and despite the circumstances, I think that says a lot.<br>
<br>
About that --- we didnt use a condom.  There could be a possibility that ---<br>
<br>
You had better not have given me anything, Luthor, she said warningly.  Lex let out a small laugh with her accusation.<br>
<br>
No, no, he protested, holding his hands up in defense, Im clean.  I meant ---<br>
<br>
O-oh, Chloe strung out with understanding.  Well, I hate to shoot down whatever hopes you might have had, but I assure you  there is no baby Luthor on the way.  A couple of years ago, my doctor put me on the pill for hormone balance issues, she explained, using her fingers to make quotation marks in the air.  Lex smiled back at her.<br>
<br>
Is it working?<br>
<br>
Hard to say, Chloe said with mock thoughtfulness.  But I really think the only reason he put me on them was because I disagreed with his archaic belief that women should be baby machines  but hey  dont look a gift horse in the mouth, right?  Otherwise, you and I could be talking about child support.  Lex threw his head back as a deep laugh released from his throat. <br>
<br>
Im fairly certain that your dad would prefer that I marry you, he finally said.  Chloe arched an eyebrow at him, not wanting to explore too deeply into the meaning behind the distinctive glint in his eye.<br>
<br>
How is he? she asked instead.  Lexs smile fell to a mere grin.<br>
<br>
He seems to be holding up remarkably well, he answered.  He was undeniably pleased when my father was arrested for assisting Luke, albeit without his knowledge; or so he claims at any rate.  Chloe snickered.<br>
<br>
Sure youre not just projecting your own feelings onto my dad? she asked.  Lex shrugged and gave her a smirk.<br>
<br>
Its entirely possible, he admitted.  So, about *us* - what do you want to do?  Chloes eyebrows rose in surprise and mirth.<br>
<br>
Youre giving me a choice? she asked somewhat teasingly.  <br>
<br>
Sure, he said, but the tone of his voice and the grin on his face suggested otherwise.<br>
<br>
Well, in that case --- she burst out in laughter at the warning look on his face.  Calm down.  I dont want to break up anymore than you do.<br>
<br>
Does that mean youre acknowledging the fact that were going out?<br>
<br>
Like Id even need to?  My own dad told me that he thinks you love me and to break it off with you now if I wasnt serious about you.  I think thats kind of a tip-off that people already know about us.<br>
<br>
He said that?<br>
<br>
Yeah.<br>
<br>
So --- *are* you serious?<br>
<br>
Chloe narrowed her eyes a little when she saw the same glint return to Lexs expression that had been there when he was talking about her father forcing him to marry her.  She couldnt stop the small chuckle that erupted from her mouth.<br>
<br>
Youre in league with my OB/GYN, arent you? she joked, but sighed and ran a hand through her already messy hair when Lex smirked at her.  Yes, Im serious, and no, Im not having your child.<br>
<br>
Eventually?<br>
<br>
Maybe.<br>
<br>
Lex grinned and rose from his seat once again to kiss her.  Their lips moved against each other for only a few moments when Lex pulled away and rested his forehead against hers, waiting for the answer to his unspoken question about *how* serious she was.  As if reading his mind, she smiled at him.<br>
<br>
I love you, she said quietly and with a hint of uncertainty.<br>
<br>
I love you too, he said and gave her another quick brush across her lips.  Any regrets?<br>
<br>
Are you suggesting I chose the wrong brother?<br>
<br>
Never; but I know this isnt going to be easy for you.  Our fathers have been taken care of, but theres still the matter of your friends.<br>
<br>
Theyll deal.<br>
<br>
And if they dont? Lex asked.<br>
<br>
Then we wont invite them to the wedding, Chloe teased.  <br>
<br>
Lexs body shook with his laughter against her.  <br>
<br>
He loved this woman.<br>
<br>
And after a battle with his brother, she loved him too.<br>
<br>
Lex leaned forward and kissed her again, her hands wrapping around the back of his neck and head to pull him closer.  <br>
<br>
He had won.  And winning was a very, very good thing.<br>
<br>
